Sentencas: Nickel oxide and yttria doped zirconia composite strength is crucial for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells, especially during transient operation, but also for the initial stacking process, where cell curvature after sintering can cause problems.
Titulo: Strength of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This work first compares tensile and ball-on-ring strength measurements of as-sintered anodes support.
Titulo: Strength of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Secondly, the strength of anode support sintered alone is compared to the strength of a co-sintered anode support with anode and electrolyte layers.
Titulo: Strength of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Finally, the orientation of the specimens to the bending axis of a co-sintered half-cell is investigated.
Titulo: Strength of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Even though the electrolyte is to the tensile side, it is found that the anode support fails due to the thermo-mechanical residual stresses.
Titulo: Strength of Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
